:: Of Course. {"position":"1550,750","size":"100,100"}
She begins to read immediately after you accept.
-
She holds one of her arms out to the side, holding a small torn piece of paper in front of her face with the other, reciting,

"O Mother of the Great Deep, we sever our love to our flesh to offer it to you alone, flaying our imperfect forms as penance for the circumstances of our births. Accept our immaciated bodies and deliver us, for we yearn to be entangled in your cold embrace as the children of your new earth."

[[*Hold your hands together and bow softly.]]
[[What does that passage mean? (+1sus)]]
[[Slowly inch away as she reads to inspect the room once more. (+1sus)|Attempt to gain your bearings.]]



